TERMS OF USE AND SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT
Please read these Terms of Use and Software License Agreement (the “Agreement”) carefully before installing Argus.
By installing and/or using Argus, you (the “Licensee”) enter into an agreement with the World Health Organization (“WHO”), and you accept and agree to comply with this Terms of Use and Software License Agreement.  

1. Components of Argus
1.1. Argus contains software developed by WHO, and has three components available: 
(i) a software to be installed on Android phones by final users (“Argus Android”); 
(ii) a software to be installed on a server (“Argus Server”); and 
(iii) a software to be installed on Android phones to operate at SMS gateways for the server (“Argus Gateway”).
This Agreement governs your use of whichever component of Argus you have downloaded and/or used through an online platform.  References to “Argus” in the remainder of this Agreement apply to any Argus component, as applicable in your particular case.  

2. Third-Party Software  
2.1. Third-party software needed to use Argus Server.  In order to run Argus, you will need to install and/or use the following third party software (i) PHP reports, (ii) MySql, (iii) Python 2.7 using Tcl/Tk and Tkinter libraries, (iv) Symphony 2 framework, (v) R, (vi) Pandoc, (vii) C3.js, (viii) D3js, and (ix) Angular (each of the above, “third-party software”). 
2.2. WHO disclaimers for third-party software. WHO makes no warranties whatsoever, and specifically disclaims any and all warranties, express or implied, that any third-party software is free of defects, virus free, able to operate on an uninterrupted basis, merchantable, fit for a particular purpose, accurate, non-infringing, or appropriate for your technical system.  
2.3. Third-party software user license(s) and use.  To the extent you are required to enter into a user license in order to use any third-party software, WHO is not a party to any such license, and WHO therefore disclaims all liability, responsibility, and/or involvement with any such license. WHO shall not be held liable or responsible for either any breach of any of the terms and conditions of any third-party software user licenses by you, or any damages arising from your use of any third-party software.
2.4. No WHO endorsement of third-party software.  The use of any third-party software does not imply that these products are endorsed or recommended by WHO in preference to others of a similar nature.
